body: An update--the original problem remains, but I was successful with cloning using --depth=1. I'll try this now with the --recursive option. Edit: this also succeeded.

@snnn any idea if this is a git issue or something wrong with this dependency? 

[submodule "cmake/external/cub"]
	path = cmake/external/cub
	url = https://github.com/NVlabs/cub.git
It looks to me like some sort of back end corruption in Github's repository. I've moved on since I got it working with a depth=1 checkout, and I'm surprised nobody else has reported it.
Yes, I just tried it again with identical results.

But I couldn't repro it.   I just tried it.
